## Core rule — Terms gate BEFORE any payment / financing click

For **every NEW** enrollment invoice: the **Terms agreement gate** MUST appear **before** the buyer can activate **any** of the following (same **`invest-pay-zone--locked`** pattern as Margarita—the zone wraps **all** such controls):

| Gated destinations (non-exhaustive) |
|-------------------------------------|
| Whop **Paid in Full** checkout |
| Whop **4-pay** checkout |
| **Splitit** (via the Whop PIF checkout path, per on-page Splitit instructions) |
| **ClarityPay** pre-qualification |
| **PayVa** pre-qualification (include **only if** CJ specifies it—never invent) |
| **Flexxbuy** pre-qualification |
| Any **future** checkout, apply, or pre-qual link added to Program Investment |

**Reason:** Financing-only prospects are still progressing on the enrollment offer—they must acknowledge the Terms **before** any payment or financing action unlocks.

**Implementation checklist:** Locked zone uses class **`invest-pay-zone`** + **`invest-pay-zone--locked`** until record succeeds; clickable prevention targets **`a.invest-btn`** (primary + **`secondary`**). Session unlock persists with **`sessionStorage`** for that browser tab.

